title: Grateful Dead Live at Knickerbocker Arena on 1992-06-12
description: Jack Straw, Sugaree, Mexicali Blues, Maggie's Farm, Brown Eyed Women, Black Throated Wind, New Speedway Boogie, Promised Land Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, Way To Go Home, Truckin'-> Smokestack Lightning-> Drums-> Jam-> The Last Time-> China Doll-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Attics Of My Life

reviews.review_text: Hot Scarlet>Fire! Trust me on this one....a smokin' and sizzlin' Scarlet>Fire.  Wow!  Grab it.
agreed was there and vividly remember it as amazing, bubbling with energy

Oh Yeah Thanks to dmilks for pointing out my error below re: Hornsby.  I knew I goofed not longer after I'd posted the review below..Vince was pretty on for this one..


Jim





Was also there for these shows and this one was just a real great time.  I always enjoyed shows at the Knick, but this was my favorite.  Great time with great friends.  Some great stuff with Jerry and Hornsby, a killer Promised Land that showed some great Vince stuff..Scarlet-Fire..unreal..a must have

The soundboard quality is great, but you get the feel of the show from the aud copy
The parking lot scene post show was loads of fun as well..

Jim

albany rocks although I don't care for this sound quality, albany always rocks! (except for 95') this was my 3rd run in albany and my favorite east coast venue. if you're like me (spoiled) the quality of this recording lacks, don't bother. 5 for the show and 3 for the sound.

GREAT sounding recording quoted: "if you're like me (spoiled) the quality of this recording lacks, don't bother. 5 for the show and 3 for the sound."

no way.  this is one of my reference discs.  its a GREAT sounding ambient recording.  awesome punch and  detail.

the FOTM brings me to tears sometimes just because its so fun and brings back so many memories.  Jerry shreds that first solo!

6/12/92 5 stars for the performance. I was there. loved it then, love it now. I recommend the AUD version over the SBD, b/c I believe the SBD is sped up.

P.S.- the gain gets cranked up during Jack Straw, so give the sound a couple minutes to get settled.

note to jhender501: Hornsby was not present for these shows. Only Wince (I mean Vince). Hornsby's official tenure with the Dead ended on 3-24-92 at The Palace.

3rd Favorite Show!! This show ramks 3rd best I ever saw behind 6/17/91 and 6/14/91.  Unfortunately there were many forgettable shows (out of 75) later in the 90's.  This AUD is probably better than the SBD.  Jerry's midi horn guitar jams are in top form during the Scarlet > Fire.  Some of the best jams of the year, maybe the decade considering we're talking about the 90's.  Check out the transition between the Scarlet and the Fire.  SICK!!!  Nice China Doll into a rippin' Sugar Magnolia.  I remember going nuts during the Sugar Mag.  Get the AUD before the SBD.

Good Times great aud recording
energy? yes, it's pretty amp'd
just came off of listening to a summer74 - portland show -- what a difference 18 years makes...

this is a 92 sign along, with MIDI's all lit up - to be sure...but this is a REALLY fun show -- definitely play it and pass it on...

5/5 = 5
